3390
05:16:36,140 --> 05:16:40,402
And I think it's important that you hear this and you are aware of it.

3391
05:16:40,582 --> 05:16:41,843
I gave you reports tonight.

3392
05:16:42,563 --> 05:16:44,745
One report was done at the beginning of the school year.

3393
05:16:45,545 --> 05:16:51,628
The second report was done this week and given to the school committee and they had a discussion on it last night.

3394
05:16:52,489 --> 05:16:57,932
And I think it's important that you know this because there are some things flying around the community that are just patently not true.

3395
05:16:58,787 --> 05:17:06,213
And I think it's important that you know it, so that when you're asked these questions in public, you can answer them truthfully, and you have the statistics in front of you.

3396
05:17:07,414 --> 05:17:12,598
I'm going to refer to the report that was given last night, because I think that's the most relevant one right now.

3397
05:17:13,679 --> 05:17:21,045
It talks about the impact of real estate development on class size, class enrollment in the Metro Public Schools.

3398
05:17:22,766 --> 05:17:24,888
And we picked eight

3399
05:17:25,617 --> 05:17:41,077
units or eight different developments in the city with 150 or more units in it and looked at the class size impact, looked at the impact of student enrollment by school, by grade.

3400
05:17:44,090 --> 05:17:48,493
by different development to give you an idea of what the impact is.

3401
05:17:49,074 --> 05:17:56,519
And if you read it closely, you'll find that there's 105 students in eight developments that come to our public schools, 105.

3402
05:17:58,321 --> 05:17:59,882
Two of them are in outside placements.

3403
05:18:02,564 --> 05:18:03,985
Two of them are in outside placements.

3404
05:18:04,865 --> 05:18:10,670
